text: Qalla Qhata (Quechua qalla carved stone, cobblestone; circular spindle disk; cheek, qhata slope, hillside, hispanicized spelling Jallacata) is a mountain in the Waytapallana mountain range in Peru, about high. It is located in the Junín Region, Huancayo Province, Huancayo District, west of Waytapallana.escale.minedu.gob.pe - UGEL map of the Huancayo Province (Junín Region) ==References== Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Junín Region
